reviewText: I am a huge fan of Sex and the city! I ordered season two and it was sent to me in a timely manor and in great condition!!

I never saw this series when it was first on TV.  I've heard it mentioned on more current TV shows (the Big Bang Theory etc).  I decided to give it a try.  I got the first one and was addicted so I bought the others as well.

Great series.  Covers, love, sex, friendship, life choices.  Entertaining and thought-provoking.  This from someone who does not watch TV.  For those who had trouble with the sleeves: remove the DVD, then take an old-style letter opener or table knife and wiggle it around in the slot to break up adhesions.
I back up all my DVDs, and this one will NOT let me back it up.  Don't waste your money if you want to do that.  Pay double the price from someone else if you want to be able to back it up.

I so love this show. It's so relatable and teaches a lot about relationships. It's funny and sad and just AMAZING!

As someone who became a fan after the series reached syndication, I was excited to purchase each season on DVD to get the full experience.  As always Amazon delivered my purchase without any issues.  I enjoyed viewing the DVD two days after ordering it.
Enjoy watching the episodes over & over again....wish they'd restart the show...asap! Or I would settle for another movie even...asap!

It was nice to see them come out with a newer box set instead of the older, bulkier sets. This new set is also cheaper than the older for some reason. This is also the last season where Carrie talks to the camera.
Love it. The slim packaging is a much better look than the bulky ones, and I love the show. This is a must have for anyone who loves Sex and the City.
Great price and great addition to my Sex in the City collection. I recommend it to anyone building their own collection. Arrives quickly and in good condition. WTG seller!

I purchased the complete series of SATC (in the pink case) and it is VERY glitchy.  Some episode won't even play, but with this one, the DVD runs fine.  No issues.  Would recommend buying the individual seasons over the complete series.
